The body style rule has a negative letter spacing:

{code}
#!css

letter-spacing: -.005em;
{code}

This results in some words rendering in a difficult to read or even misleading manner.  Consider the word "disclaimer".  With negative letter spacing the &#x27;c&#x27; and &#x27;l&#x27; characters collide and appear to be the letter &#x27;d&#x27;.  I thought I had created a project called "disdaimer".

Another issue caused by this spacing is that words ending in some characters appear to be chopped off.  For example, the right-most tips of the letter &#x27;x&#x27; is clipped in the word "box".

For both of these examples the words I&#x27;m using were displayed in the repository list, so if you&#x27;re dead set on squishing characters please consider at least removing it for the repo list, but IMO the site text is much easier to read with default letter spacing.

Thank you for your consideration.

To reproduce:

# On a new or current wiki, create a new link:

{code}
#!python

* [API REST](api-rest)

{code}

# Click through the link, and it should give you the option to edit.
# Once you edit, you&#x27;ll notice three fields, but the &#x27;Content&#x27; field doesn&#x27;t load the visual text editor

For example if I use links in comments, preview function doesn&#x27;t render this.

Instead of I see this in preview:

{code}
[Link text](url)
{code}

Hello.

When I run this query:

{code}
/2.0/repositories/<ACCOUNT>/<REPO>/refs/branches?fields=-links&format=json
{code}

Links node is included in the response.

{code}
/2.0/repositories/<ACCOUNT>/<REPO>/refs/branches?fields=-target.%2A&format=json
{code}

Or

{code}
/2.0/repositories/<ACCOUNT>/<REPO>/refs/branches?fields=-target&format=json
{code}

Target node is included in the response.

According to documentation: https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/meta/partial-response\\
I should be able to return all/additional fields when running this query:

{code}
/2.0/repositories/<ACCOUNT>/<REPO>/refs/branches?fields=%2A&format=json
{code}

But response is exactly the same as before.

Is it possible to include PR link/state in branches query ?

Thank you and have a nice day.

